'''Fcitx''' (Free Chinese Input Toy for X) is a Chinese input method. You can install Fcitx by using the following command:

{{Emerge|app-i18n/fcitx}}

== Use Flags ==

{{USEflag|package=app-i18n/fcitx
|cairo+yes+
|gtk++yes
|pango+yes+
|table+yes++Adds suppport for Wubi, Erbi & etc.
|debug
|gtk3
|opencc
|qt+++Lets you use fcitx in qt programs
|static-libs
|zhengma+++Adds support for Zhengma
}}

Note: If you want to use Fcitx in Gtk2, Gtk3 or Qt programs, you need to add gtk, gtk3 or qt in USE.

== Using Fcitx ==

In order to use Fcitx in X, you need to add these environment variables(such as ~/.xinitrc, ~/.*shrc)(You need to <code>export</code> them after setting these variables):

<pre>LANG=zh_CN.UTF-8
LC_ALL=
XIM=fcitx
XIM_PROGRAM=fcitx
XMODIFIERS="@im=fcitx"
QT_IM_MODULE=xim
GTK_IM_MODULE=xim</pre>

Note: If you want to use Fcitx in English language, you may add <code>LC_CTYPE=zh_CN.UTF-8</code> in environment.

== Configuration ==

You can edit Fcitx's configuration file at <code>~/.config/fcitx/config</code>.

Also, there is a tool to configure Fcitx called {{Package|fcitx-configtool}}, which is in the Gentoo-zh [[overlay]]. (You may need to add the '~arch' keyword).

